{"id": "EUVD-2024-53313", "enisaUuid": "69a0f295-333d-37d1-82d3-febf300d8099", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nbpf,perf: Fix invalid prog_array access in perf_event_detach_bpf_prog\n\nSyzbot reported [1] crash that happens for following tracing scenario:\n\n  - create tracepoint perf event with attr.inherit=1, attach it to the\n    process and set bpf program to it\n  - attached process forks -> chid creates inherited event\n\n    the new child event shares the parent's bpf program and tp_event\n    (hence prog_array) which is global for tracepoint\n\n  - exit both process and its child -> release both events\n  - first perf_event_detach_bpf_prog call will release tp_event->prog_array\n    and second perf_event_detach_bpf_prog will crash, because\n    tp_event->prog_array is NULL\n\nThe fix makes sure the perf_event_detach_bpf_prog checks prog_array\nis valid before it tries to remove the bpf program from it.\n\n[1] https://lore.kernel.org/bpf/Z1MR6dCIKajNS6nU@krava/T/#m91dbf0688221ec7a7fc95e896a7ef9ff93b0b8ad", "datePublished": "2024-12-27T15:31:56", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-03T21:32:00", "baseScore": 5.5, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H", "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/842e5af282453983586e2eae3c8eaf252de5f22f", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/c2b6b47662d5f2dfce92e5ffbdcac8229f321d9d", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/dfb15ddf3b65e0df2129f9756d1b4fa78055cdb3", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/978c4486cca5c7b9253d3ab98a88c8e769cb9bbd", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2024-56665", "https://lists.debian.org/debian-lts-announce/2025/03/msg00001.html"], "aliases": ["CVE-2024-56665"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.05, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "619bd2a9-6a24-3386-bbd9-b4154482c48b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "21db2f35fa97e4a3447f2edeb7b2569a8bfdc83b <c2b6b47662d5f2dfce92e5ffbdcac8229f321d9d"}, {"id": "80d0c777-9ef7-3dfc-b6d5-f06c7c8ab951", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "0ee288e69d033850bc87abe0f9cc3ada24763d7f <dfb15ddf3b65e0df2129f9756d1b4fa78055cdb3"}, {"id": "80e19981-3eb8-3587-9911-3bc0d997b92d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "7a5c653ede645693422e43cccaa3e8f905d21c74 <842e5af282453983586e2eae3c8eaf252de5f22f"}, {"id": "93ef2a4a-66e6-3ffd-aaa6-2d4393c8733f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.12.6"}, {"id": "995b45f7-f150-3c63-8e1b-e9ede90df77b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "0ee288e69d033850bc87abe0f9cc3ada24763d7f <978c4486cca5c7b9253d3ab98a88c8e769cb9bbd"}, {"id": "bb92fc42-2231-35bd-84a7-e6353aef121e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.13"}, {"id": "ce1e383a-e85f-393a-b3a8-5ddada47893e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.1.121"}, {"id": "d225a06a-2a32-351b-92ba-be6812133906", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "d8347c5c-80ec-3984-9b80-0d2443e4bc6c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.12"}, {"id": "e70e5749-20de-39fa-9950-a5bb07a6ea7c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "585674b9d0d80bd7f428b1f88be13cf6d5d6f739"}, {"id": "f8745b26-1ca3-3d8a-bd03-8b85263ad6ab", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "b4007d5fe38625b8a1b8edc0f385d86527651238"}, {"id": "fcfe4636-de09-3150-afc3-0ca82c32464b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.6.67"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "14645938-3d5d-3e84-8872-86ba1951be7b", "vendor": {"name": "Linux"}}], "isExploited": false}